\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 In a large bowl, whip together amaretto, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cinnamon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cinnamon}}, heavy cream and confectioners' sugar until soft peaks form.\
In a medium bowl, combine the pistachios and ricotta and stir in half of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 whipped cream}}. Gently fold in the remaining whipped cream. Fill a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pastry-bag/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pastry bag}} with no tip with the mixture to fill the cannoli shells.\
Dip the tips of the cannoli into the melted {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chocolate/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chocolate}}. Place the sheet tray in the refrigerator for 2 hours or until filling and chocolate is set.\
